The paper deals with entropy and information theory, which is closely related to the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the behavior of solutions to the p-nonlinear heat equation, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of probability densities and concavity also suggests that the paper could be relevant to statistical inference (cs.ST) or machine learning (cs.LG).
